'''Edward John "Jack" Hazlett''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|MNZM|size=85%}} (21 July 1938 – 16 December 2014) was a New Zealand [[rugby union]] player. A [[Rugby union positions#Prop|prop]], Hazlett represented [[Southland Rugby Football Union|Southland]] at a provincial level, and was a member of the New Zealand national side, the [[All Blacks]], in 1966 and 1967. He played 12 matches for the All Blacks including six internationals.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://stats.allblacks.com/asp/Profile.asp?ABID=371 |title = Jack Hazlett | last = Knight | first = Lindsay | publisher = New Zealand Rugby Union | accessdate = 22 December 2014}}</ref>
